# Monity API Endpoints Reference

## Base URL

- **Development**: `http://192.168.18.41:3000/api/v1`
- **Production**: Configured via environment variables

## Authentication Endpoints

All auth endpoints are under `/auth` prefix:

### Public Endpoints (No Authentication Required)

- `POST /auth/register` - User registration
- `POST /auth/login` - User login

### Protected Endpoints (Authentication Required)

- `GET /auth/profile` - Get user profile
- `GET /auth/financial-health` - Get user's financial health metrics

## Transaction Endpoints

All transaction endpoints are under `/transactions` prefix and require authentication:

### CRUD Operations

- `GET /transactions` - Get all transactions (with optional filters)
- `GET /transactions/recent` - Get recent transactions
- `GET /transactions/:id` - Get transaction by ID
- `POST /transactions` - Create new transaction
- `PUT /transactions/:id` - Update transaction
- `DELETE /transactions/:id` - Delete transaction

### Legacy Endpoints (for frontend compatibility)

- `POST /transactions/add-expense` - Add expense (automatically sets typeId=1)
- `POST /transactions/add-income` - Add income (automatically sets typeId=2)

## Category Endpoints

All category endpoints are under `/categories` prefix and require authentication:

- `GET /categories` - Get all categories
- `POST /categories` - Create new category
- `PUT /categories/:id` - Update category
- `DELETE /categories/:id` - Delete category

## Budget Endpoints

All budget endpoints are under `/budgets` prefix and require authentication:

- `GET /budgets` - Get all budgets
- `POST /budgets` - Create new budget
- `PUT /budgets/:id` - Update budget
- `DELETE /budgets/:id` - Delete budget

## Balance Endpoints

All balance endpoints are under `/balance` prefix and require authentication:

- `GET /balance/all` - Get overall balance
- `GET /balance/savings-overview` - Get savings overview
- `GET /balance/:month/:year` - Get monthly balance
- `GET /balance/history` - Get balance history

## AI Endpoints

All AI endpoints are under `/ai` prefix and require authentication:

- `POST /ai/suggest-category` - Get AI category suggestion for transaction
- `POST /ai/feedback` - Record AI feedback
- `GET /ai/projections` - Get projected expenses
- `GET /ai/stats` - Get AI statistics

## User Endpoints

All user endpoints are under `/users` prefix and require authentication:

- `GET /users/search` - Search users

## Additional Endpoints

- `GET /months` - Get available months (requires authentication)
- `GET /savings-goals` - Savings goals management (requires authentication)
- `GET /groups` - Group management (requires authentication)
- `GET /invitations` - Invitation management (requires authentication)
- `GET /subscription-tier` - Subscription management (requires authentication)
- `GET /financial-projections` - Financial projections (requires authentication)

## Admin Endpoints

All admin endpoints are under `/admin` prefix and require admin role:

- Various admin management endpoints (see [admin.ts](mdc:backend/routes/admin.ts))

## Authentication

- All protected endpoints require `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header
- Tokens are obtained from `/auth/login` or `/auth/register` endpoints
- Token is stored in AsyncStorage with key `auth_token`

## Rate Limiting

- General API routes: Standard rate limiting
- Auth routes: Stricter rate limiting for security
- Applied via middleware in [index.ts](mdc:backend/routes/index.ts)

## Frontend Integration

The frontend uses [apiService.ts](mdc:frontend/Monity/app/src/services/apiService.ts) which provides:

- Automatic token management
- Request/response logging
- Error handling
- TypeScript interfaces for all data types
